2026-05-17 19:50:35 | DEBUG | strands_evaluation.instrumentation.agent_plugins | Model response #4 [role=assistant block=1 tool_use] execute_ideal({"code": "import pandas as pd\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n# load files from the download manifest\nimport json\nmanifest_path = Path('DOWNLOAD_MANIFEST_PATH')\n# read the actual path map from the provided path in environment\nwith open('/home/ec2-user/eval_eqa/exploratory-qa-eval/.sandbox_isolated/task_1760530_1779047399385/.download_manifest.json','r') as f:\n    manifest = json.load(f)\npath_map = manifest['path_map']\n\nfiles = [\n    path_map['s3://sana-kramabench/datagov/kramabench-legal-hard-14/files/csn-data-book-2024-csv/CSVs/State MSA Identity Theft data/Connecticut.csv'],\n    path_map['s3://sana-kramabench/datagov/kramabench-legal-hard-14/files/csn-data-book-2024-csv/CSVs/State MSA Identity Theft data/Massachusetts.csv'],\n    path_map['s3://sana-kramabench/datagov/kramabench-legal-hard-14/files/csn-data-book-2024-csv/CSVs/State MSA Identity Theft data/Maine.csv'],\n    path_map['s3://sana-kramabench/datagov/kramabench-legal-hard-14/files/csn-data-book-2024-csv/CSVs/State MSA Identity Theft data/NewHampshire.csv'],\n    path_map['s3://sana-kramabench/datagov/kramabench-legal-hard-14/files/csn-data-book-2024-csv/CSVs/State MSA Identity Theft data/RhodeIsland.csv'],\n]\n\n# read and normalize each file\nall_rows = []\nfor p in files:\n    df = pd.read_csv(p, skiprows=2, header=None, names=['Metropolitan Area','# of Reports'])\n    # strip quotes and commas\n    df['Metropolitan Area'] = df['Metropolitan Area'].astype(str).str.strip('\"')\n    df['# of Reports'] = df['# of Reports'].astype(str).str.replace(',','').str.strip('\"')\n    df = df[df['# of Reports'].notna() & (df['# of Reports']!='')]\n    df['# of Reports'] = pd.to_numeric(df['# of Reports'], errors='coerce')\n    all_rows.append(df)\n\nbig = pd.concat(all_rows, ignore_index=True)\n# Also include Vermont and Maine and Connecticut already included; Ve